This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=5057

Buftabline takes over the tabline and renders the buffer list in it instead of a tab list. It is designed with the ideal that it should Just Work: drop it into your setup and you&#039re done. There is only minimal configurable behavior.

Screenshot, rationale and comparisons with other plugins available at
https://github.com/ap/vim-buftabline
